[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST is too weak to open 1\H but just right for 2\H.

Wow! WEST has 21 HCP and two good \Hs. Could this be time for a slam try?

Nope, no slam here. Suppose EAST has six \Hs headed by the AK. The trump suit 
would certainly be solid, but then EAST couldn't possibly have an outside Ace as well or he would have been 
too strong for a Weak-two opening. So WEST just bids 4\H.}

